HEADWORD: Lone-Star State
<hw>Lone-Star State</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>Texas; -- a nickname
alluding to the single star on its coat of arms, being the device used
on its flag and seal when it was a republic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

